snippet.textDisplay:
Sharing my own interpretation of the whole EP here. I maybe wrong but that‚Äôs just how I glued the pieces. This EP is a masterpiece. üëåüèΩ

To start.... the way I see it, she wasn‚Äôt really talking about a particular person here but rather it‚Äôs about life in general. She personified ‚Äúlife‚Äù, talking about it as if it‚Äôs a real person. 

In Umm... Life, Bibi starts the story with finding herself in such a crappy state. That‚Äôs why it‚Äôs the first track. It sets the premise and she was basically saying she‚Äôs having tough time with ‚Äúlife‚Äù. (Edit: in the song, she shares that she often gets asked by people why she looks like that or what happened to her but no one seem to actually care what she‚Äôs got to say. So every time they ask her what happened, she just responds with ‚Äúumm... life‚Äù. Life happened.)

In Bad Sad and Mad, she goes into details on why she‚Äôs in such a bad state. She used BDSM as a metaphor. There‚Äôs no guy (or girl üòâ) here. And let‚Äôs make it clear, BDSM is NOT abuse but a CONSENSUAL power play. Here, ‚Äúlife‚Äù is the dominant party taking over her, hurts her - the way she described in the song and Bibi as the submissive one, letting ‚Äúlife‚Äù beat her up and even taking pleasures out of it - feeling like she deserved it - that‚Äôs why she lets herself suffer with it.

Piri the Dog is her comparing herself to a stray or lost dog - feeling overwhelmed, lost and scared of ‚Äúlife‚Äù, looking for comfort and a home. It‚Äôs a song full of despair - like a call for help, masked in a light, quirky song. ‚òπÔ∏è

Birthday Cake is when she realized she has been selling herself short all along  - that she has a gift/talent she can enjoy and she can do or achieve many things with it but she kept it to herself because ‚Äúnobody told her‚Äù. She keeps repeating the line ‚ÄúI allow myself to lose it‚Äù but notice how she changed it to ‚ÄúCOULDN‚ÄôT allow myself to lose it‚Äù in the last line. In short, OUR GIRL FINALLY REALIZED HER WORTH. 
(Note: you maybe wondering why it‚Äôs called Birthday Cake... bday cakes are gifts üëâüèº talents are also gifts. I think?Smart!)

Lastly, Life‚Äôs a Bitch is a conclusion to this story. She‚Äôs saying that yes, life‚Äôs a bitch but she won‚Äôt let it take over and run over her again. This time, she‚Äôs taking control of her life and live it the way she wants to.

PS: Bibi, if you‚Äôre reading this, please blink twice if I got it right (or partly right. I‚Äôll take it. üòÇ)
